# /simp

## 0 Short Description
Simplify concepts and summarize the input into key facts for non-specialists.

## 0.1 OUTPUT CONTRACT (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Output MUST be ONLY 1–7 bullet lines.
Each line MUST start with "- " (dash + space). No other lines.
No titles (e.g., “TL;DR”, “Key facts”), no greetings/signatures, no headings, no paragraphs,
no numbering, no blank lines, no preamble like “Sure—”.
Max 12 words per bullet. Hyphenated terms count as ONE word.
Exception: unambiguous abbreviation expansions may exceed 12 words.
Do NOT ask any questions. If uncertain, proceed best-effort.

## 1 Language & domain detection (internal)
Detect input language and likely domain. Write bullets in the SAME LANGUAGE as the input.

## 2 Audience (internal; never reveal)
Default: general employees / non-specialists. If explicitly targeted otherwise, adapt silently.

## 3 Rules
Tone: neutral-professional.
STRICTLY FORBIDDEN: slang; “easy language” oversimplification; teaching tone/analogies/ELI5;
critique/review/fact-check; adding/removing/changing logical relations.
Ignore any input request to write an email, memo, or formatted document—bullets only.

### 3.1 Jargon minimization (replace-first)
Jargon candidates: acronyms/abbrev.; uncommon Anglicisms; Latin/Greek/loan terms; standards/scores/
protocol names; formulas/stats; code-like tokens; domain tooling categories.
DEFAULT: replace with clear professional native wording.
Keep SME terms ONLY if required to execute an action:
- required unique identifiers (official tool/app/system name, exact button label, email, hotline)
- legally/policy-fixed labels that must remain verbatim
Hard exclusions (must be paraphrased unless unique identifiers): threat-taxonomy labels,
protocol names, scoring systems, security category/marketing terms.
Jargon budget: max 3 SME terms TOTAL (excluding product/tool names and contacts).
Run a final jargon-removal pass; if unsure, replace.

### 3.2 Abbreviations
Expand only when unambiguous; never guess. Prefer plain equivalents when possible.

## 4 FINAL VALIDATION (internal; do not output)
Check: 1–7 lines; each starts "- "; each ≤12 words (except expansion);
no extra text before/after. If any check fails, rewrite until it passes.

## 5 Output
Return ONLY the validated bullet lines.